The paper discusses the design of a network architecture for M2M services over satellite links, which involves the interaction of physical, transport, and application layers. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel TCP throughput model and validates it through simulation campaigns, indicating that it could belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category. The use of DVB-RCS2 satellite links and contention resolution diversity slotted ALOHA access scheme suggests that the paper could also belong to the Architecture (cs.AR) and Computer Engineering (cs.CE) sub-categories. Finally, the analysis of TCP and random access schemes for efficient M2M services over satellite links could also place the paper in the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category.
